WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:28.720
- Mm. I can't find the right form.
You'll have to come back in an hour.

3
00:00:28.720 --> 00:00:32.040
- Nope. The bosses need to book
their pool inspection.

4
00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:34.200
- I'm needed in the council meeting.

5
00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:37.400
- An online booking system would
be more efficient and less archaic.

6
00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:39.520
- Hmm. You're a motel cleaner.
Saffron.

7
00:00:39.520 --> 00:00:42.360
- And you're pushing
your luck. Sheree.

8
00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:44.440
- I really need to get
to that meeting.

9
00:00:44.440 --> 00:00:47.480
- All right.
Also on the agenda for today. um...

10
00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:51.360
a matter that's really
close to my heart.
- Not the bloody cats again.

11
00:00:51.360 --> 00:00:55.200
- They are vicious predators.
- Honestly. who voted her on?

12
00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:58.560
She's bonkers.
- These cats are killing
our native birdlife.

13
00:00:58.560 --> 00:01:01.880
They need to be banned from
Mowai Bay and the entire peninsula.

14
00:01:04.400 --> 00:01:07.040
That's good.
That's really good.

15
00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:09.040
- Fill it in during business hours.
Monday to Friday.

16
00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:12.200
- Nope. I'll fill it now and book
the pool inspection... now.

17
00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:15.920
- You have to pay a fee.
and I don't have time to
fire up the EFTPOS machine.

18
00:01:15.920 --> 00:01:18.600
- Yes. I do clean a motel. Sheree.

19
00:01:18.600 --> 00:01:22.760
A motel with a pool.
which people can't swim in if
the council doesn't inspect it.

20
00:01:22.760 --> 00:01:27.640
And if people can't swim.
they're in their rooms making
a mess. which I have to clean.

21
00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:30.440
- Most business owners diarise
when their pool inspection is due.

22
00:01:30.440 --> 00:01:33.560
not leave it till the last minute
like your bosses have.

23
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.400
- They're new. They make mistakes.

24
00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:40.680
Whereas you've been behind this desk
since that blouse was in fashion...

25
00:01:40.680 --> 00:01:42.680
the first time round.

26
00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:50.400
- You think our native
birdlife dying is funny?
- It's a human right to own a pet.

27
00:01:50.400 --> 00:01:54.280
- And it's my right to wanna live
in a world with trees and birdlife.
- No one's stopping ya.

28
00:01:54.280 --> 00:01:58.080
- You decide you wanna cut
a native tree. and suddenly
the bylaws are changed.

29
00:01:58.080 --> 00:02:00.960
- t's a hazard.
- No. it's not.

30
00:02:00.960 --> 00:02:04.880
It's blocking your sea view.
- Look ― what I do on my property
is none of your business.

31
00:02:04.880 --> 00:02:07.200
- And the dotterelsaremy business.

32
00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:09.520
I propose that we ban
domestic cats by the year―

33
00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:13.760
- I propose that this meeting
is over. It's 1 o'clock.

34
00:02:13.760 --> 00:02:15.760
Sheree.
- Oh.

35
00:02:19.840 --> 00:02:22.320
- Huh?

36
00:02:22.320 --> 00:02:23.800
Oh― Thank you.

37
00:02:23.800 --> 00:02:25.680
- Pool inspection's booked
for Tuesday.

38
00:02:25.680 --> 00:02:28.600
- Brilliant. Thank you. Saffron.
- Sweet. See you tomorrow.

39
00:02:28.600 --> 00:02:31.600
- Oh. hang on. hang on.
You've still got the beachfront
units to turn around.

40
00:02:31.600 --> 00:02:35.080
- But I went to the council for you.
- You volunteered to go.

41
00:02:35.080 --> 00:02:39.160
- Yeah. because I didn't
want to do the beachfront units.
and I helped you skip the queue.

42
00:02:39.160 --> 00:02:41.680
It was gonna be three weeks
for an inspection.
- Really?

43
00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:45.920
- So I roughed up the receptionist.
- Nah. she's joking. Vin.

44
00:02:45.920 --> 00:02:47.920
You're joking. right?

45
00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:51.560
- Oh my God. fine.
I'll do the beachfront units.

46
00:02:51.560 --> 00:02:53.600
- Well. she booked
the pool inspection.

47
00:03:24.160 --> 00:03:27.240
- Gordon's not here.
He doesn't vote.

48
00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:30.200
- I've tried calling him several
times. but he didn't answer.

49
00:03:30.200 --> 00:03:32.880
- Gordon's never late.
- Sheree. go and check on him.

50
00:03:32.880 --> 00:03:36.360
- Me? Why me?
- Cos you're not a councillor.

51
00:03:37.240 --> 00:03:41.320
Fine. Let's take a break
while we wait for Gordon.

52
00:03:42.440 --> 00:03:46.240
Anyone for a non-binary
gingerbread person?

53
00:03:56.880 --> 00:03:58.880
- Gordon.

54
00:04:03.160 --> 00:04:05.160
Hello. Gordon.

55
00:04:12.840 --> 00:04:14.840
Gordon?

56
00:04:15.600 --> 00:04:17.600
Gordon!

57
00:04:23.880 --> 00:04:28.320
-  can't get it out of
my head. I just can't unsee it.

58
00:04:28.320 --> 00:04:32.480
His own cat.
- Uh. I don't―
I don't think that the. um...

59
00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:34.680
Sorry. I'll be right back.

60
00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:37.920
- Hey.
- Hey. um... this is a big one.

61
00:04:38.600 --> 00:04:42.600
Homicide. Head of Mowai Council.
- City Homicide on the way?

62
00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:45.680
- Yeah. Um...
I just wanted another check through.

63
00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:48.560
Gotta get my initial report right.

64
00:04:55.960 --> 00:04:57.960
- Huh.
- Yeah.

65
00:05:11.920 --> 00:05:13.960
- Well. the cat's innocent.

66
00:05:13.960 --> 00:05:16.440
- Unless the floof
can hold a knife.

67
00:05:16.440 --> 00:05:19.040
- Multiple stab wounds.
Is there a murder weapon?

68
00:05:19.040 --> 00:05:22.280
- Uh. the initial sweep
didn't turn anything up.

69
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:25.880
- All right.
Well. let's take a look around.

70
00:05:42.560 --> 00:05:44.560
- Hello. Hey.

71
00:05:44.760 --> 00:05:48.400
Hey. what's going on?
Is that a cop car out the front?

72
00:05:48.400 --> 00:05:50.400
- Yeah. Uh...

73
00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:54.840
You a friend of Gordon's?
- Yeah.

74
00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:56.920
Why? What's he done now?

75
00:05:56.920 --> 00:05:59.080
- Mate. I'm really sorry.

76
00:06:31.760 --> 00:06:33.760
- Jamie.

77
00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:38.960
- I'll bag it.
- And. um...

78
00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:43.840
- ...dust the dishwasher...
- ...for prints.
- You got it.

79
00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:47.120
- When was the last
time you saw him?
- Uh. a couple weeks ago.

80
00:06:47.120 --> 00:06:50.800
We usually catch up on
a Friday night. but...

81
00:06:50.800 --> 00:06:54.280
he took a rain check.
He said he was seeing a lady.

82
00:06:54.280 --> 00:06:56.280
- Any idea who?
- No.

83
00:06:56.360 --> 00:06:58.440
Shit. A home invasion...

84
00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:01.320
in Mowai Bay. it's just―
it's unbelievable.

85
00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:06.000
- So you're a local. then?
- Yeah. The wife and I are up
on the hill above the main road.

86
00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:10.760
- So how do you know Gordon?
- This used to be my grandpa's place.

87
00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:14.440
Yeah. so he passed away 10 years
ago. and Gordon bought it.

88
00:07:14.440 --> 00:07:16.680
The place was in good hands.

89
00:07:16.680 --> 00:07:20.680
Gordon might've looked like
a suit. but... nah.

90
00:07:21.880 --> 00:07:26.880
He was a good guy.
- I'll grab your number in case
Constable Haira has any questions.

91
00:07:26.880 --> 00:07:30.800
Gordon had a date on Friday night.
- ID on that date?

92
00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:33.560
- Negative. Mobile phone?
- I haven't seen one.

93
00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:38.600
There was a knife in the dishwasher.
so someone had the presence of mind
to cover their tracks.

94
00:07:38.600 --> 00:07:42.520
Get rid of any prints. DNA.
- And not have to take
the murder weapon with him.

95
00:07:42.520 --> 00:07:46.040
- Premeditation.
- Can I help you?

96
00:07:46.040 --> 00:07:49.840
- Uh... these are my consultants ―
from Australia.

97
00:07:49.840 --> 00:07:52.440
- Pete Coleman. My wife. Vinny.

98
00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:57.680
- The people who run a motel.
- And 20 years with
the New South Wales Police Force.

99
00:07:57.680 --> 00:08:00.520
- Constable Haira requested
a second look over the scene.

100
00:08:00.520 --> 00:08:04.240
- He's bagged a clean kitchen knife.
Possibly a match for the victim's
stab wounds.

101
00:08:04.240 --> 00:08:07.480
- Yeah. thanks for that. We'd like
to keep the scene secure. so...

102
00:08:07.480 --> 00:08:10.560
- Of course. Absolutely.
We'll. um... We'll leave you to it.
detective...?

103
00:08:10.560 --> 00:08:14.040
- Grainger ― Annette ―
Northern Homicide.

104
00:08:18.920 --> 00:08:21.840
Constable. what are
these prints? A dog?

105
00:08:21.840 --> 00:08:25.120
- Uh. Gordon's cat.
Haven't seen it yet.

106
00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:28.360
- She was―
- Don't say it. Vin.

107
00:08:28.360 --> 00:08:31.600
- She was an arsehole.
Just an observation.

108
00:08:31.600 --> 00:08:35.680
- And if the roles were reversed?
You're investigating a scene.
and two randoms are there.

109
00:08:35.680 --> 00:08:40.280
- It's a big case. Surely all...
hands on deck is a good thing.

110
00:08:40.280 --> 00:08:42.440
- Uh. a― am I allowed to go?

111
00:08:42.760 --> 00:08:45.760
- Uh. you found the body here?
- I did.

112
00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:49.680
Sheree Rothery. Yes. Gordon
was late to a council meeting.

113
00:08:49.680 --> 00:08:53.160
so I came to...
find him.

114
00:08:53.320 --> 00:08:57.200
- Well. if Constable Haira's taken
your statement. you can go home.
- He has. so thank you.

115
00:08:57.200 --> 00:09:01.440
- Oh. and Sheree. if you need
support or to talk to anyone.
you just reach out.

116
00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:03.440
- I'm fine. thank you.

117
00:09:05.880 --> 00:09:10.040
- Well. at least Detective Grainger
has finally shown up.
- Hmm.

118
00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:13.040
- Dogs will wait till they're
starving. but cats...

119
00:09:13.040 --> 00:09:15.520
they'll just go for it.
They'll eat their owner right up.

120
00:09:15.520 --> 00:09:17.800
- The cat did not eat Gordon.

121
00:09:18.720 --> 00:09:21.200
But it has disappeared.
- Just like his mobile phone.

122
00:09:21.200 --> 00:09:23.560
Have you got that number. S―?

123
00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:25.560
Thank you.

124
00:09:26.120 --> 00:09:29.240
- If the killer has Gordon's phone.
they're not gonna answer it.

125
00:09:29.240 --> 00:09:30.960
- This is Gordon.
Leave a message.

126
00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:32.560
- Well. they didn't
turn it off either.

127
00:09:32.560 --> 00:09:34.720
- And what are you two doing
about this homicide?

128
00:09:34.720 --> 00:09:38.160
- The police have it
under control. Maxine.
- Well. this is terrifying.

129
00:09:38.160 --> 00:09:41.960
- Poor Sheree. man. First
she gets bullied at work. and―
- By you.

130
00:09:41.960 --> 00:09:44.480
- Yeah. and then she finds
her ex-boyfriend dead.

131
00:09:44.480 --> 00:09:48.640
- Sheree and Gordon were together?
-Brutalbreak up. too.

132
00:09:48.640 --> 00:09:51.640
- Honey. did you notice Sheree.
when she was leaving. her―?
- The handbag.

133
00:09:51.640 --> 00:09:53.640
Yeah. I did.

134
00:09:56.920 --> 00:10:00.520
- Comms to Mowai Bay.
- Yeah. Mowai Bay here.

135
00:10:00.520 --> 00:10:04.400
- Need you on a 2R. Someone's driven
a digger into Mowai Estuary.

136
00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:09.200
- Copy. 1W? Wait. that's the code
for water rescue. right?

137
00:10:09.240 --> 00:10:12.920
- Nah. there's no one inside.
It's just a digger.

138
00:10:12.920 --> 00:10:15.960
- I'm scene guarding a homicide.
 mean. a one...

139
00:10:15.960 --> 00:10:17.920
- All good. constable?

140
00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:20.480
- Yeah. Just a 2R.
Nothing to worry about.

141
00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:25.240
- Off you go. then.
- But it's just―
It's not urgent.

142
00:10:25.240 --> 00:10:28.320
- 10-2. Constable Haira's
on his way.

143
00:10:28.880 --> 00:10:30.880
We got this. Toodle-oo.

144
00:10:33.080 --> 00:10:34.680
Yeah. sorry about that. mate.

145
00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:38.360
- Thanks for meeting with us.
- We realise it's been a hard day.

146
00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:40.800
- Oh. it just doesn't feel real.

147
00:10:40.800 --> 00:10:44.000
I mean. those... cat prints.
I just...

148
00:10:44.480 --> 00:10:48.680
I never trusted that cat.
It wasn't a friendly one.

149
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:54.320
- Sheree. how long were
you and Gordon together?
- Seven months.

150
00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:57.800
He broke it off a few weeks ago.
but we were fine.

151
00:10:57.800 --> 00:11:02.600
In fact. we had a drink here
Friday evening. He was giving me
the last of my things.

152
00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:05.840
- Why didn't he
give you those things at
the council meeting on Friday?

153
00:11:05.840 --> 00:11:09.400
- Well. he didn't like to mix
his work life and personal.

154
00:11:09.400 --> 00:11:12.080
Which is. you know.
ultimately why he ended things.

155
00:11:12.080 --> 00:11:15.000
- So you have a drink here.
then you go home.

156
00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:18.480
You didn't go back to his place?
- He didn't invite me.

157
00:11:18.480 --> 00:11:21.160
- Did Gordon have his phone
with him while you were here?

158
00:11:21.160 --> 00:11:24.040
- Um. well. probably. I don't know.

159
00:11:24.520 --> 00:11:27.920
- OK. I might. um...
might grab a beer after all.

160
00:11:27.920 --> 00:11:29.920
You want one?
- Yeah.

161
00:11:30.080 --> 00:11:33.880
- So what will happen to the cat?
I'm assuming it'll be put down.

162
00:11:33.880 --> 00:11:35.920
- Uh. it hasn't turned up yet.

163
00:11:35.920 --> 00:11:39.720
And you know as well as I do
the cat didn't kill Gordon.

164
00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:43.600
Two phones?

165
00:11:43.600 --> 00:11:45.720
- No.

166
00:11:45.720 --> 00:11:48.960
I meant. yeah.
- Oh. well. feel free
to answer the other one.

167
00:11:48.960 --> 00:11:53.240
- Oh. no. It's fine. They can wait.
- No. no. I insist.

168
00:11:55.960 --> 00:12:00.360
- Hello. Sheree speaking.
- Gidday. Sheree.

169
00:12:03.400 --> 00:12:07.200
- Do you wanna tell us why you
have your dead ex-boyfriend's phone?

170
00:12:11.760 --> 00:12:14.280
- I'm so sorry.
- No. no. no. no. It's OK.

171
00:12:14.280 --> 00:12:16.280
Just... take your time.

172
00:12:19.440 --> 00:12:23.120
- It was on the kitchen
counter...

173
00:12:23.120 --> 00:12:25.160
and  grabbed it.
and I ran.

174
00:12:25.160 --> 00:12:28.280
- So Gordon's lying there.
and the first thing you do
is look for his phone.

175
00:12:28.280 --> 00:12:31.840
- I needed to get out of there.
I mean. what if she was
still in the house?

176
00:12:31.840 --> 00:12:33.840
- She?
- Rachel.

177
00:12:33.840 --> 00:12:37.560
The cat. And when I got outside.
I called 111.

178
00:12:37.600 --> 00:12:40.800
- From Gordon's phone?
- Oh...

179
00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:43.040
From my own.

180
00:12:44.480 --> 00:12:46.480
OK. The truth.

181
00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:50.400
- Yes. please.
- Late Friday night. I...

182
00:12:51.080 --> 00:12:53.080
texted him a few times.

183
00:12:53.680 --> 00:12:56.360
and phoned him. and left some...

184
00:12:57.720 --> 00:12:59.320
impolite messages.

185
00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:01.800
It was after a bottle
of Chardonnay at home.

186
00:13:01.800 --> 00:13:06.160
- The thing is. Sheree.
taking the victim's phone
from the crime scene...

187
00:13:06.160 --> 00:13:08.440
makes you look really guilty.

188
00:13:08.440 --> 00:13:11.520
- But I thought
I'd look bad if anyone ever
saw or read the messages.

189
00:13:11.520 --> 00:13:15.960
- Depending on the timeline
and GPS pinging. those messages
might actually clear you.

190
00:13:15.960 --> 00:13:17.960
- Really?

191
00:13:20.400 --> 00:13:22.240
The problem is.
I couldn't get into it.

192
00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:26.960
- Well. she said she tried Gordon's
birthday and her birthday.
What else can we try?

193
00:13:26.960 --> 00:13:31.240
Hey. why are you still here?
- I fell asleep in Unit 9.

194
00:13:31.680 --> 00:13:34.120
Well. don't worry. I won't charge you
for the extra three hours I was here.

195
00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:39.320
- This is Gordon's phone?
Are you trying to break into it?

196
00:13:39.320 --> 00:13:42.680
- We'd like to.
- You know I love me
a code-cracking challenge.

197
00:13:42.680 --> 00:13:46.640
- We should give it to Jamie
and the homicide detective.

198
00:13:46.640 --> 00:13:50.920
- Well. it can't hurt. Just. like.
a little― just a little sneaky peek.

199
00:13:50.920 --> 00:13:53.280
- All right. Well.
if Saffron can get into it.

200
00:13:53.280 --> 00:13:56.200
- If? Give me a star sign
and a favourite band.

201
00:13:56.200 --> 00:13:59.400
and I can get into
anybody's business.

202
00:14:09.920 --> 00:14:12.240
- Enjoy your stay.

203
00:14:12.240 --> 00:14:15.240
- Hey. Cole.
What do you make of this?

204
00:14:15.640 --> 00:14:17.640
Reid. Ryder. Marshall.

205
00:14:17.640 --> 00:14:20.320
- Send them through to me.
I'll check them out.

206
00:14:20.320 --> 00:14:23.480
- Hey. guys. Someone from
the council's arrived to see you ―

207
00:14:23.480 --> 00:14:25.680
about poor Gordon. maybe.

208
00:14:26.480 --> 00:14:28.480
- Pool inspection.

209
00:14:34.600 --> 00:14:37.800
We triple-checked the measurements.

210
00:14:39.720 --> 00:14:42.640
- What was your name?
- Poppy McMahon.

211
00:14:42.640 --> 00:14:45.400
- Tragedy about Gordon.
What do you think happened?
- Vin. Vin.

212
00:14:45.400 --> 00:14:49.320
Should we let her focus
on the inspection first?

213
00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:51.320
- Was he well liked?

214
00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:56.280
- We're all grieving and shaken up. I
mean. Gordon was a fellow councillor.

215
00:14:56.280 --> 00:14:58.880
Just hope the rest of us are safe.
- Safe?

216
00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:01.560
- Council business
isn't all sunshine and rainbows.

217
00:15:01.560 --> 00:15:04.560
- You have to make
unpopular decisions.
- Just like this one.

218
00:15:04.560 --> 00:15:08.200
This is a fail.
- Why?
- Hinges are too slow to self-close.

219
00:15:08.200 --> 00:15:10.520
Get your hinges sorted.
and go for another inspection.

220
00:15:10.520 --> 00:15:14.040
- Shit. I mean.
does that mean we have to pay
