anything or anyone?

485
00:31:25.480 --> 00:31:27.880
- You didn't notice the blood
on the cat's paws?

486
00:31:27.880 --> 00:31:30.960
- No. It was da― dark.
I didn't notice.

487
00:31:31.440 --> 00:31:35.120
I just put him in there.

488
00:31:35.960 --> 00:31:39.400
Look ― I see how this appears.
but I didn't kill Gordon.

489
00:31:39.400 --> 00:31:43.720
He was a horrible human being.
but I save creatures.
 don't kill them.

490
00:31:43.720 --> 00:31:47.360
- Yeah. I'm gonna have to get
you to stick around. Poppy.

491
00:31:47.360 --> 00:31:50.800
I'll call Detective Grainger.
get her to come back
and take a statement.

492
00:31:50.800 --> 00:31:52.360
- Oh...

493
00:31:52.360 --> 00:31:55.240
OK. You don't want us to―
- Yeah. That's― That's great.

494
00:31:55.240 --> 00:31:58.080
Thanks. Jamie. We'll see ya.
- Thanks.

495
00:31:58.080 --> 00:32:00.560
Oh. uh... one favour. though.

496
00:32:01.080 --> 00:32:03.080
- Yeah. What do you need?

497
00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:08.480
- No more saying yes to favours
until we know what they are.

498
00:32:08.480 --> 00:32:10.880
- Wha― It wants to sleep with us.

499
00:32:10.880 --> 00:32:13.840
- Well. there's only room
for two in this bed.

500
00:32:13.840 --> 00:32:16.840
- Aw.
- Come on. sweetie.

501
00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:21.400
- Aw.

502
00:32:24.040 --> 00:32:27.600
I'll get Gordon's mate Lincoln
to pick her up tomorrow.
- Mm-kay.

503
00:32:27.600 --> 00:32:30.520
- Good girl.

504
00:32:34.600 --> 00:32:37.280
OK.

505
00:32:39.040 --> 00:32:41.040
Night.

506
00:32:46.320 --> 00:32:48.320
- Mm.

507
00:32:49.280 --> 00:32:51.280
Is it later?

508
00:32:51.520 --> 00:32:53.520
- What?

509
00:32:54.280 --> 00:32:56.600
- Is that you touching my leg?

510
00:32:56.600 --> 00:32:58.560
- No.

511
00:32:58.560 --> 00:33:00.560
- Oh!

512
00:33:03.440 --> 00:33:05.440
Oh. honey.

513
00:33:13.040 --> 00:33:15.880
- I'll take her up to
Gordon's sister in Auckland.

514
00:33:15.880 --> 00:33:18.640
Wish I could keep the poor thing.
but wife's allergic.

515
00:33:18.640 --> 00:33:19.960
- Hi.
- Hey.

516
00:33:19.960 --> 00:33:22.600
- Yeah. I wish we could keep her.
too. but. um...

517
00:33:22.600 --> 00:33:25.760
I don't want to.

518
00:33:25.760 --> 00:33:27.760
- So. Poppy McMahon. eh?

519
00:33:28.160 --> 00:33:30.120
Thinks cats are vicious killers.

520
00:33:30.120 --> 00:33:32.560
but we must protect
the great whites at all costs.
- Right.

521
00:33:32.560 --> 00:33:34.560
- Well. thanks again.

522
00:33:34.560 --> 00:33:37.720
It's really good of you.
- No. happy to go up
to the big smoke.

523
00:33:37.720 --> 00:33:40.480
T20's on at Eden Park.
- Ah. Cricket.

524
00:33:40.480 --> 00:33:43.600
Yeah. the wife and I are more.
uh― more AFL.

525
00:33:43.600 --> 00:33:47.400
- They say there's no such thing
as a perfect woman. but first
day I met Jodie.

526
00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:50.320
she's wearing the. uh―
the classic brown and beige shirt.

527
00:33:50.320 --> 00:33:52.760
It's the old school uniform
for the Kiwi cricket team.

528
00:33:52.760 --> 00:33:55.920
I knew right then and there ―
she's the one.

529
00:33:55.920 --> 00:33:58.120
- Nothing like love
at first sight. eh?

530
00:33:58.120 --> 00:34:00.400
Enjoy the cricket.
- See ya.

531
00:34:04.600 --> 00:34:08.200
Thank you. You're gonna
get a medal for this.

532
00:34:08.200 --> 00:34:13.200
- Medal?
- Constable Haira is going to
Barren Island to rescue Jewel.

533
00:34:13.200 --> 00:34:15.600
- Oh.
- And the other five cats.

534
00:34:15.600 --> 00:34:18.000
- Aw.

535
00:34:18.480 --> 00:34:20.960
I mean.
it's an important job. Jamie.

536
00:34:20.960 --> 00:34:22.960
- Yeah. nah.

537
00:34:23.000 --> 00:34:26.400
Annette's doing all
the important jobs.
- Is she?

538
00:34:26.400 --> 00:34:31.600
- Hey. The tyre track that Cole
took a photo of at Gordon's.
- Mm.

539
00:34:34.040 --> 00:34:36.920
- That's the digger
I dragged out of the estuary.

540
00:34:36.920 --> 00:34:38.920
- It's a match.

541
00:34:38.920 --> 00:34:41.240
Well done. my husband.
- Mm.

542
00:34:41.240 --> 00:34:45.480
So. Annette
is searching Gordon's computer.
looking for a rental agreement.

543
00:34:45.480 --> 00:34:48.080
Or did they drive there in it...

544
00:34:49.240 --> 00:34:51.120
and then drive it away?

545
00:34:51.120 --> 00:34:54.000
- What. like a getaway
digger?

546
00:34:54.000 --> 00:34:57.280
- Or maybe Gordon's
planning some work.

547
00:34:58.000 --> 00:35:00.400
- Well. no way to find out now.

548
00:35:01.960 --> 00:35:03.960
- Well. there is.

549
00:35:07.080 --> 00:35:10.880
- Poppy murdered Gordon.
That is horrifying.

550
00:35:11.360 --> 00:35:16.120
but not surprising.
- She's helping police
with inquiries.

551
00:35:16.120 --> 00:35:21.320
- Gotcha.
- Sheree. was Gordon planning any
kind of building at his property?

552
00:35:21.320 --> 00:35:24.920
- No. He loved that old house.
- Nothing he'd need
an excavator for?

553
00:35:24.920 --> 00:35:27.920
- Not that I know of.
So. was it about the cats?

554
00:35:27.920 --> 00:35:31.800
